---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';

const deepSelectorProblem = `.page .wrapper .content .card .title {
    margin: 0;
}`;

const deepSelectorFix = `.product-card > .title {
    margin: 0;
}`;

const specificityProblem = `#app .product-list .product-card .title {
    color: red !important;
}`;

const specificityFix = `@layer components, theme;

@layer theme {
    .product-card > .title {
        color: red;
    }
}`;

const utilityProblem = `<article class="p-l m-b-xl bg-dark text-light radius-m grid gap-m">
    ...
</article>`;

const utilityFix = `<article class="product-card product-card--featured">
    ...
</article>`;

const rootFileProblem = `site.css
    8,000 lines
    all components
    all layouts
    all hacks`;

const rootFileFix = `components/
    product-card.css
    site-header.css
    filter-panel.css`;

const thirdPartyProblem = `@import './vendor/slider.css';`;
const thirdPartyFix = `@import './vendor/slider.css' layer(legacy);`;

const randomValuesProblem = `.card {
    padding: 17px;
    border-radius: 13px;
    color: #4a2cff;
}`;

const randomValuesFix = `.card {
    padding: var(--space-m);
    border-radius: var(--br-m);
    color: var(--colour-accent);
}`;

const stateProblem = `.button--loading {}
.button--disabled {}
.button--active {}`;

const stateFix = `.button {}
.button.is_loading {}
.button.is_disabled {}`;
---

<DocsLayout
    title="CSS Anti-pattern Gallery"
    description="Common CSS architecture anti-patterns and modern LSCSS fixes."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Anti-pattern gallery</p>

        <h1>
            CSS anti-pattern gallery
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            Most CSS disasters start as small shortcuts. These examples show
            what breaks, why it breaks, and how LSCSS avoids the slow descent
            into selector archaeology.
        </p>
    </section>

    <nav class="section-nav" aria-label="Anti-pattern sections">
        <a href="#deep-selectors">Deep selectors</a>
        <a href="#specificity">Specificity</a>
        <a href="#utilities">Utilities</a>
        <a href="#random-values">Random values</a>
        <a href="#state">State</a>
    </nav>

    <section id="deep-selectors" class="content-block">
        <h2>Deep selectors</h2>

        <div class="anti-pattern-pair">
            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--bad">
                <h3>Problem</h3>
                <pre><code>{deepSelectorProblem}</code></pre>
                <p>Deep selectors couple styles to markup structure and become difficult to override.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--good">
                <h3>Fix</h3>
                <pre><code>{deepSelectorFix}</code></pre>
                <p>Use shallow scoped component selectors.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="specificity" class="content-block">
        <h2>Specificity escalation</h2>

        <div class="anti-pattern-pair">
            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--bad">
                <h3>Problem</h3>
                <pre><code>{specificityProblem}</code></pre>
                <p>IDs and important declarations create override battles.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--good">
                <h3>Fix</h3>
                <pre><code>{specificityFix}</code></pre>
                <p>Use layer order before increasing specificity.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="utilities" class="content-block">
        <h2>Utility overload</h2>

        <div class="anti-pattern-pair">
            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--bad">
                <h3>Problem</h3>
                <pre><code>{utilityProblem}</code></pre>
                <p>Too many utilities hide component intent and ownership.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--good">
                <h3>Fix</h3>
                <pre><code>{utilityFix}</code></pre>
                <p>Use semantic components and keep utilities rare.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="random-values" class="content-block">
        <h2>Random values everywhere</h2>

        <div class="anti-pattern-pair">
            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--bad">
                <h3>Problem</h3>
                <pre><code>{randomValuesProblem}</code></pre>
                <p>Magic numbers and random colours destroy consistency fast.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--good">
                <h3>Fix</h3>
                <pre><code>{randomValuesFix}</code></pre>
                <p>Use tokens so spacing, colour, and radius stay consistent.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="state" class="content-block">
        <h2>State disguised as modifiers</h2>

        <div class="anti-pattern-pair">
            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--bad">
                <h3>Problem</h3>
                <pre><code>{stateProblem}</code></pre>
                <p>Temporary UI state gets mixed with reusable component variants.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--good">
                <h3>Fix</h3>
                <pre><code>{stateFix}</code></pre>
                <p>Use modifiers for variants and .is_* classes for temporary state.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>Massive root files</h2>

        <div class="anti-pattern-pair">
            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--bad">
                <h3>Problem</h3>
                <pre><code>{rootFileProblem}</code></pre>
                <p>Large root files make ownership and review harder.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--good">
                <h3>Fix</h3>
                <pre><code>{rootFileFix}</code></pre>
                <p>Keep root files as import maps, not dumping grounds.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>Third-party CSS leakage</h2>

        <div class="anti-pattern-pair">
            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--bad">
                <h3>Problem</h3>
                <pre><code>{thirdPartyProblem}</code></pre>
                <p>Unlayered third-party CSS can unexpectedly dominate project styles.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="anti-pattern-card anti-pattern-card--good">
                <h3>Fix</h3>
                <pre><code>{thirdPartyFix}</code></pre>
                <p>Isolate third-party CSS in a low-priority legacy layer.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>
</DocsLayout>
